post_text:
PRS students - join in the fun! SPIRIT WEEK begins TODAY! Send in your pictures!

Movement Monday - Get active and snap a picture - send it in!!
Tuesday - Dress like an essential worker - take a picture to show your thanks!!
Wednesday - Earth Day - Take a nature walk, clean up trash, do your part to help the earth - send in your pics!!
Thursday - Show us your artwork - art is an anything you create!!
Friday - Rest & Read - Snap a pic of you reading in your favorite PJ's

Pictures should be sent to prsteam@portnj.org OR added to https://photos.app.goo.gl/gva9rLCv2cyy45ec9 before 5 pm each day.

shared_text:
Cape May County Zoo AAZK Chapter
September 2, 2019 at 8:58 AM ·

Sending out a huge THANK YOU to the students at Port Republic School for donating $1,450 so we could buy new toys for the animals!! You all are AMAZING!! We purchased a BIG hamster wheel for the bat-eared fox, a fun raft for the otters, a new ball for the snow leopards, tons of likit treats for the goats and bongos, tamarind pods for the primates, over $300 in bird treats, and treats for the keepers for Zookeeper Week!

This donation was given in memory of Trigger Nass, the beloved dog of one of the 8th graders that passed away before his time.🐶 💔

Communities Coming Together:
Last night, in our on going effort to continue to improve safety and security, Galloway Township Police Department, Galloway Township Ambulance Squad, Port Republic Volunteer Fire Company and Port Republic School District came together in what was the 1st of many Emergency Management Training Drills. Thank you to all who participated and organized this event.

post_text: Congratulations to Ms. Stewart and the 8th grade class. With the help of the 7th grade class, they made and served pancake breakfast to families, friends, community members of Port Republic and neighboring communities and raised over $600.00 at the Port Republic School Annual Pancake Breakfast!!!! The message below was sent from Cedar Creek Trunk or Treat Coordinator:

Due to the weather forecasted for Saturday, Trunk-or-Treat at Cedar Creek High School has been canceled. We apologize for any inconvenience to those who planned on attending; however, due to the severity of the weather forecasted, the safety of everyone involved is our top priority.

We look forward to continuing our Halloween tradition next year. Thank you for your continued support of Cedar Creek!

post_text:
The PTS is looking for candidates for upcoming Executive Board elections!

Are you a volunteer extraordinaire? Do you love nothing more than seeing a smile on your child's face? If you like to be the Leader of the Pack, Partner in Crime, stating the facts or playing with numbers, then becoming an Executive Board Member for the Port Republic PTS is the thing for you!!

Executive Board Members are needed for the 2017/18 School year (two year term) for following positions:
President
Vice President
Secretary
Treasurer

Please remember new members and volunteers are always welcome!!!

We look forward to working together with you in the future to create a fun and memorable environment for our children.

Leslie, Jessica, Shirley & Julie
